@startuml
' Intent Definition MS - Sequence Flow
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #dae8fc
skinparam participantBorderColor #6c8ebf
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam noteBorderColor #d6b656
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff2cc
skinparam dividerBackgroundColor #f0f0f0
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #f9f9f9

title Intent Definition MS (ID MS): Primary Process Sequence Flows:

actor "External Client\n/ OEX / Authorised Platform" as Client
participant "NGW\n(user context terminates here)" as GW
participant "Intent Definition MS\n(ID MS)" as IDMS
collections "IntentSpecification\nCatalogue" as CAT
database "Outbox Table\n(DB)" as OUTBOX
database "Subscription\nRegistry (DB)" as SUBREG
participant "Outbox Dispatcher\n(background worker)" as DISPATCHER
actor "External Subscriber\nSystem" as SUB

note over GW, IDMS
  NGW forwards trusted system/service context downstream.
  End-user context does not propagate past NGW.
end note

== 1. Create New Draft IntentSpecification: ==
Client -> GW : POST /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification\nTMF-compliant IntentSpecification request\n{ name, version, specKey, ... }
(no lifecycleStatus on create; isBundle optional/default false)
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity

group Atomic DB transaction:
  IDMS -> CAT : Persist new DRAFT IntentSpecification
  IDMS -> OUTBOX : Write IntentSpecificationCreateEvent row\n{ status: PENDING }
end

IDMS --> GW : 201 Created\nETag + Location + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
GW --> Client : 201 Created\nETag + Location + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification

|||
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Poll for PENDING event rows
OUTBOX --> DISPATCHER : [IntentSpecificationCreateEvent]
DISPATCHER -> SUBREG : Lookup subscriptions matching eventType
SUBREG --> DISPATCHER : [{ subscriptionId, callbackUrl }]
loop for each matched subscription:
  DISPATCHER -> SUB : HTTPS POST to subscriber-owned callbackUrl\nHTTP webhook; no external Kafka\nTMF-aligned event payload\n{ eventType: IntentSpecificationCreateEvent, event, eventId, eventTime, ... }
  alt HTTP 2xx:
    SUB --> DISPATCHER : 200 OK / 202 Accepted
    DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Mark event row DELIVERED
  else HTTP error / timeout:
    SUB --> DISPATCHER : 4xx / 5xx / timeout
    DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Increment retry count\nexponential back-off; dead-letter after max retries
  end
end

== 2. Retrieve / List IntentSpecifications: ==
Client -> GW : GET /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification\nor GET /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/{id}
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
IDMS -> CAT : Query catalogue for discovery / validation support
CAT --> IDMS : IntentSpecification list or single resource
IDMS --> GW : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification representation
GW --> Client : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification representation
note over Client, CAT : Read-only operation — no outbox event written.

== 3a. Full-Replacement Update (preferred PUT): ==
note over Client, IDMS
  PUT is the preferred platform extension for deterministic full replacement.
  Specification must be DRAFT.
  If-Match is required.
end note
Client -> GW : PUT /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/draft/{draftId}\nIf-Match: "<etag>"\n{ complete IntentSpecification resource }
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
alt Missing If-Match:
  IDMS --> GW : 428 Precondition Required\n{ code: PRECONDITION_REQUIRED, reason: IF_MATCH_REQUIRED }
  GW --> Client : 428 Precondition Required
else Stale / mismatched ETag:
  IDMS --> GW : 412 Precondition Failed\n{ code: PRECONDITION_FAILED, reason: ETAG_MISMATCH }
  GW --> Client : 412 Precondition Failed
else If-Match valid and resource is DRAFT:
  group Atomic DB transaction:
    IDMS -> CAT : Replace DRAFT IntentSpecification
    IDMS -> OUTBOX : Write IntentSpecificationAttributeValueChangeEvent row
  end
  IDMS --> GW : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
  GW --> Client : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
end

|||
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Poll for PENDING AttributeValueChangeEvent
OUTBOX --> DISPATCHER : [IntentSpecificationAttributeValueChangeEvent]
DISPATCHER -> SUBREG : Lookup matching subscriptions
SUBREG --> DISPATCHER : [{ callbackUrl }]
DISPATCHER -> SUB : HTTPS POST to subscriber-owned callbackUrl\nTMF-aligned webhook event payload\nNo external Kafka delivery
SUB --> DISPATCHER : 200 OK / 202 Accepted
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Mark DELIVERED

== 3b. Partial Update (supported but discouraged PATCH): ==
note over Client, IDMS
  PATCH is supported for TMF compatibility but discouraged for ordinary edits.
  Specification must be DRAFT.
  If-Match is required.
end note
Client -> GW : PATCH /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/draft/{draftId}\nIf-Match: "<etag>"\n{ partial fields }
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
alt Missing If-Match:
  IDMS --> GW : 428 Precondition Required\n{ code: PRECONDITION_REQUIRED, reason: IF_MATCH_REQUIRED }
  GW --> Client : 428 Precondition Required
else Stale / mismatched ETag:
  IDMS --> GW : 412 Precondition Failed\n{ code: PRECONDITION_FAILED, reason: ETAG_MISMATCH }
  GW --> Client : 412 Precondition Failed
else If-Match valid and resource is DRAFT:
  group Atomic DB transaction:
    IDMS -> CAT : Apply controlled partial update to DRAFT IntentSpecification
    IDMS -> OUTBOX : Write IntentSpecificationAttributeValueChangeEvent row
  end
  IDMS --> GW : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
  GW --> Client : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
end

== 4. Activate Draft and Auto-Retire Previous Active Version: ==
note over Client, IDMS
  Activation is represented as lifecycleStatus change.
  Service does not expose POST .../intentSpecification/{id}/activate.
  Active lifecycle values are DRAFT, ACTIVE, and RETIRED.
  DELETED is not an IntentSpecification lifecycleStatus.
end note
Client -> GW : PUT or PATCH /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/draft/{draftId}\nIf-Match: "<etag>"\n{ lifecycleStatus: "ACTIVE" }
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
alt Missing If-Match:
  IDMS --> GW : 428 Precondition Required
  GW --> Client : 428 Precondition Required
else Stale / mismatched ETag:
  IDMS --> GW : 412 Precondition Failed
  GW --> Client : 412 Precondition Failed
else If-Match valid:
  group Atomic DB transaction:
    IDMS -> CAT : Set target spec lifecycleStatus = ACTIVE
    IDMS -> CAT : Find previous ACTIVE spec with same specKey and set RETIRED
    IDMS -> OUTBOX : Write IntentSpecificationStatusChangeEvent\n{ lifecycleStatus: ACTIVE }
    IDMS -> OUTBOX : Write IntentSpecificationStatusChangeEvent\n{ lifecycleStatus: RETIRED, previousSpecId }
  end
  IDMS --> GW : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
  GW --> Client : 200 OK\nETag + TMF-compliant IntentSpecification
end

|||
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Poll for PENDING status-change events
OUTBOX --> DISPATCHER : [StatusChange(ACTIVE), StatusChange(RETIRED)]
DISPATCHER -> SUBREG : Lookup matching subscriptions
SUBREG --> DISPATCHER : [{ callbackUrl }]
DISPATCHER -> SUB : HTTPS POST to subscriber-owned callbackUrl\nTMF-aligned IntentSpecificationStatusChangeEvent\n{ lifecycleStatus: "ACTIVE" }
SUB --> DISPATCHER : 200 OK / 202 Accepted
DISPATCHER -> SUB : HTTPS POST to subscriber-owned callbackUrl\nTMF-aligned IntentSpecificationStatusChangeEvent\n{ lifecycleStatus: "RETIRED", id: previousSpecId }
SUB --> DISPATCHER : 200 OK / 202 Accepted
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Mark both events DELIVERED

== 5. Delete Unused Draft IntentSpecification: ==
note over Client, IDMS
  Delete is an operation/outcome, not a DELETED lifecycle state.
  Allowed only for DRAFT resources when retention and runtime-reference rules permit.
  If-Match is required.
end note
Client -> GW : DELETE /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/{id}\nIf-Match: "<etag>"
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
alt Missing If-Match:
  IDMS --> GW : 428 Precondition Required\n{ code: PRECONDITION_REQUIRED, reason: IF_MATCH_REQUIRED }
  GW --> Client : 428 Precondition Required
else Stale / mismatched ETag:
  IDMS --> GW : 412 Precondition Failed\n{ code: PRECONDITION_FAILED, reason: ETAG_MISMATCH }
  GW --> Client : 412 Precondition Failed
else Retention / runtime-reference rule violation:
  IDMS -> CAT : Validate DRAFT status and no active runtime references
  CAT --> IDMS : Conflict
  IDMS --> GW : 409 Conflict\n{ reason }
  GW --> Client : 409 Conflict\n{ reason }
else Deletion permitted:
  group Atomic DB transaction:
    IDMS -> CAT : Remove IntentSpecification / apply retention policy
    IDMS -> OUTBOX : Write IntentSpecificationDeleteEvent row
  end
  IDMS --> GW : 204 No Content
  GW --> Client : 204 No Content
end

|||
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Poll for PENDING DeleteEvent
OUTBOX --> DISPATCHER : [IntentSpecificationDeleteEvent]
DISPATCHER -> SUBREG : Lookup matching subscriptions
SUBREG --> DISPATCHER : [{ callbackUrl }]
DISPATCHER -> SUB : HTTPS POST to subscriber-owned callbackUrl\nTMF-aligned IntentSpecificationDeleteEvent\nNo external Kafka delivery
SUB --> DISPATCHER : 200 OK / 202 Accepted
DISPATCHER -> OUTBOX : Mark DELIVERED

== 6a. Register External Event Subscription: ==
note over Client, SUBREG
  ID MS uses the domain-scoped hub route for IntentSpecification events.
  Subscriber callback URLs are subscriber-owned.
  Hub notifications are delivered as REST webhooks, not Kafka.
end note
Client -> GW : POST /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/hub\n{ callback: "https://subscriber.example/notify",\n  query: "eventType=IntentSpecificationCreateEvent" }
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
IDMS -> SUBREG : Persist { subscriptionId, callbackUrl, filter, deliveryMetadata }
SUBREG --> IDMS : Created subscription
IDMS --> GW : 201 Created\nLocation + ETag + subscription representation
GW --> Client : 201 Created\nLocation + ETag + subscription representation

== 6b. Retrieve External Event Subscription: ==
Client -> GW : GET /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/hub/{id}
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
IDMS -> SUBREG : Lookup subscription record
SUBREG --> IDMS : Subscription
IDMS --> GW : 200 OK\nETag + subscription representation
GW --> Client : 200 OK\nETag + subscription representation

== 6c. Delete External Event Subscription: ==
Client -> GW : DELETE /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/hub/{id}\nIf-Match: "<etag>"
GW -> IDMS : Forward request using system/service identity
alt Missing If-Match:
  IDMS --> GW : 428 Precondition Required\n{ code: PRECONDITION_REQUIRED, reason: IF_MATCH_REQUIRED }
  GW --> Client : 428 Precondition Required
else Stale / mismatched ETag:
  IDMS --> GW : 412 Precondition Failed\n{ code: PRECONDITION_FAILED, reason: ETAG_MISMATCH }
  GW --> Client : 412 Precondition Failed
else If-Match valid:
  IDMS -> SUBREG : Remove subscription record
  SUBREG --> IDMS : Removed
  IDMS --> GW : 204 No Content
  GW --> Client : 204 No Content
end

@enduml


/
Note: ID MS uses specKey -> id, draftId selects mutable DRAFT candidate, and official version is assigned only on activation. Runtime IC MS uses concrete ACTIVE intentSpecification.id, not specKey or draftId.
/
